87
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:58,150
The Emperor doesn't come even when the Empress Dowager is buried?

88
00:07:58,150 --> 00:07:59,970
I heard from a protocol officer

89
00:07:59,970 --> 00:08:04,400
that the Emperor got sick from grief while keeping vigil,

90
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:09,020
so he now only prays for the Empress Dowager in the palace

91
00:08:09,020 --> 00:08:10,910
and can't come.

92
00:08:14,870 --> 00:08:18,500
You were an officer, so do you know these people?

93
00:08:19,190 --> 00:08:20,390
Over there.

94
00:08:20,390 --> 00:08:24,460
The head of civil officers, Minister of Personnel,

95
00:08:24,460 --> 00:08:28,410
Grand Secretary of Zhongji Hall, Shi Yiping.

96
00:08:28,410 --> 00:08:33,670
He is prudent. He can be considered the official with the most integrity.

97
00:08:34,410 --> 00:08:37,260
Next to him is the Minister of Revenue,

98
00:08:37,260 --> 00:08:40,900
Grand Secretary of Jianji Hall, Zhao Bingwen.

99
00:08:40,900 --> 00:08:45,370
He is the Deputy Chief Grand Secretary, prideful and noble.

100
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:47,260
At the head of the military officers

101
00:08:47,260 --> 00:08:50,480
is Zhuang Luyin, the Marquis of Pingjin,

102
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:52,340
the Defender General of the Nation back then

103
00:08:52,340 --> 00:08:55,260
and current Grand Master for Glorious Happiness.

104
00:08:55,260 --> 00:08:58,500
Vice Minister of Works, Zhuang Zhifu, is his son.

105
00:08:58,500 --> 00:09:01,980
Chu Huaiming is their lackey.

106
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:13,420
Kneel!

107
00:09:19,020 --> 00:09:24,320
Send the Empress Dowager's casket for burial.

108
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:12,050
Final step.

109
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:14,200
Check the paint on the coffin.

110
00:10:25,930 --> 00:10:27,200
Official,

111
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:31,160
the Empress Dowager's casket has the Big Dipper on it.

112
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:33,140
What does that mean?

113
00:10:33,140 --> 00:10:36,290
The emperor's residence is called Zichen.

114
00:10:36,290 --> 00:10:37,450
After their deaths,

115
00:10:37,450 --> 00:10:40,420
the emperors wanted to reside in Zichen, which is guarded by the Big Dipper.

116
00:10:40,420 --> 00:10:42,290
They not only carved this design into their coffins

117
00:10:42,290 --> 00:10:44,670
but also, I believe, placed the Empress Dowager's body

118
00:10:44,670 --> 00:10:47,810
in this position for burial.

119
00:10:47,810 --> 00:10:53,320
Do you think we can live in Zichen after we die?

120
00:10:58,260 --> 00:10:59,840
Let's go.

121
00:11:20,870 --> 00:11:24,240
Gentlemen, I'm here to send you off.

122
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:28,750
Come with me.

123
00:11:58,080 --> 00:12:01,390
Here's some good wine and food prepared for you.

124
00:12:01,390 --> 00:12:05,150
You should know they are poisoned.

125
00:12:05,150 --> 00:12:08,220
You won't feel any pain after eating them.

126
00:12:08,220 --> 00:12:12,180
After three days, you will die peacefully.

127
00:12:21,450 --> 00:12:24,020
Just a death.

128
00:12:24,020 --> 00:12:26,590
Why speak so much?

129
00:12:33,510 --> 00:12:37,560
Live out these three days well and go to heaven in peace.

130
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:08,100
This is Magu Wine from Jianchang Prefecture.

131
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:11,830
I heard it's about 300 wen per liang.

132
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:14,710
Open it.

133
00:13:18,630 --> 00:13:21,170
Good wine really is different.

134
00:13:21,170 --> 00:13:23,510
It smells so good.

135
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:45,200
Kneel!

136
00:13:53,860 --> 00:13:56,850
Bow!

137
00:14:09,030 --> 00:14:12,190
Straighten up!

138
00:14:12,770 --> 00:14:15,140
The mechanism has been turned on.

139
00:14:15,140 --> 00:14:20,770
Then he'll soon see the surprise we've prepared for him.

140
00:14:21,390 --> 00:14:25,420
I really want to see what Zang Hai's face will look like then.

141
00:14:28,770 --> 00:14:31,140
Do you know what this is?

142
00:14:31,140 --> 00:14:32,440
Venison.

143
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:33,860
Have you ever eaten it?

144
00:14:33,860 --> 00:14:38,200
I used to hunt it, but in the end, they were taken by the town's security unit,

145
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:40,920
so I've never tried it either.

146
00:14:44,810 --> 00:14:49,770
Numbing ourselves can be a way of life.

147
00:14:49,770 --> 00:14:55,030
An old friend of mine once told me that someday,

148
00:14:55,030 --> 00:14:58,750
he was going to put an end to the system of burial sacrifices,

149
00:14:58,750 --> 00:15:03,200
but he couldn't achieve it, and I failed even more.

150
00:15:03,720 --> 00:15:08,550
Maybe our descendants will be able to someday.

151
00:15:08,550 --> 00:15:10,830
If we expect our descendants to do everything for us,

152
00:15:10,830 --> 00:15:13,910
their lives will only get worse.

153
00:15:13,910 --> 00:15:17,600
How can we live in this world with dignity?

154
00:15:18,290 --> 00:15:21,730
The second bow!

155
00:15:40,550 --> 00:15:42,600
Are you thirsty?

156
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:47,120
How about I taste it for you first?

157
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:49,000
Good point. We all die sooner or later,

158
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:50,780
it would be better to become a well-fed ghost.

159
00:15:50,780 --> 00:15:52,900
Come on. We can't get out anyway.

160
00:15:52,900 --> 00:15:54,100
I'll drink first.

161
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:56,670
- Let me quench my thirst. 
 - Don't drink.

162
00:15:57,840 --> 00:16:01,520
If you drink, you really can't get out.

163
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:03,430
What do you mean?

164
00:16:03,430 --> 00:16:06,900
Do you mean you still want to get out?

165
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:10,030
Don't think about it anymore, and don't try to persuade us.

166
00:16:10,030 --> 00:16:13,150
Just let us get drunk till our deaths.

167
00:16:15,290 --> 00:16:16,740
I have a way out.

168
00:16:16,740 --> 00:16:18,460
A way out?

169
00:16:21,140 --> 00:16:24,490
The third bow!

170
00:16:29,430 --> 00:16:31,280
What's your idea?

171
00:16:31,280 --> 00:16:33,980
Did you secretly dig an escape well?

172
00:16:33,980 --> 00:16:35,340
That's not allowed!

173
00:16:35,340 --> 00:16:37,220
Secretly digging an escape well in the royal tomb

174
00:16:37,220 --> 00:16:38,820
is a cardinal sin that will get all our families executed.

175
00:16:38,820 --> 00:16:39,850
- Yes. 
 - Yes.

176
00:16:39,850 --> 00:16:41,530
No.

177
00:16:41,530 --> 00:16:43,960
We'll leave through the gate.

178
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:46,290
That great entrance of the tomb.

179
00:16:46,290 --> 00:16:48,840
We'll walk out gloriously in the open.

180
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:54,860
You're going to lead us out in the open?

181
00:16:54,860 --> 00:16:58,030
The fourth bow!

182
00:17:04,490 --> 00:17:07,060
Straighten up!

183
00:17:07,060 --> 00:17:09,920
The ceremony won't be over until the Dragon-Cracking Stone falls,

184
00:17:09,920 --> 00:17:11,210
and the officials are all there.

185
00:17:11,210 --> 00:17:14,100
If we go out at that time, they'll see us.

186
00:17:14,100 --> 00:17:16,690
- That's right. 
 - That's what I want them to see.

187
00:17:16,690 --> 00:17:19,540
We're going to walk out in plain sight.

188
00:17:19,540 --> 00:17:21,340
How is that possible?

189
00:17:21,340 --> 00:17:24,670
If we go out in front of all those people, they'll beat us to death with sticks.

190
00:17:24,670 --> 00:17:26,510
- That's right. 
 - And that would involve our families.

191
00:17:26,510 --> 00:17:31,360
If we don't fight, others will continue to be buried alive.

192
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:35,630
Your families might even be next.

193
00:17:54,380 --> 00:17:56,160
How can we fight?

194
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:58,140
Just us?

195
00:17:58,620 --> 00:18:00,380
That's right.

196
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:05,110
What is your plan?

197
00:18:05,110 --> 00:18:06,990
If we can make it to the entrance of the tomb

198
00:18:06,990 --> 00:18:08,530
before the Dragon-Cracking Stone falls,

199
00:18:08,530 --> 00:18:13,990
I have the confidence to put an end to this burial and get them to let us out.

200
00:18:19,380 --> 00:18:21,380
You really think you can do it?

201
00:18:23,550 --> 00:18:25,160
I believe you.

202
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:28,490
Tell us what to do.

203
00:18:31,620 --> 00:18:34,410
Finish!

204
00:18:34,410 --> 00:18:39,040
Drop the Dragon-Cracking Stone!

205
00:19:08,490 --> 00:19:10,400
This door is not the Dragon-Cracking Stone.

206
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:11,820
It can be opened.

207
00:19:11,820 --> 00:19:13,200
The mechanism is outside.

208
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:17,190
True, but there must be a pull-wire switch connected to the tomb door.

209
00:19:17,190 --> 00:19:21,950
All we need to do is find that pull-wire switch to manipulate the outside mechanism.

210
00:19:24,170 --> 00:19:25,300
I know.

211
00:19:25,300 --> 00:19:28,680
The pull-wire switch that connects to the tomb door mechanism is up there.

212
00:19:40,690 --> 00:19:42,780
It's this brick. Guys, come and help.

213
00:19:42,780 --> 00:19:45,090
- Okay. 
 - Okay.

214
00:19:48,060 --> 00:19:49,410
Bring up the stools.

215
00:19:49,410 --> 00:19:51,230
- Okay. 
 - Okay.

216
00:19:59,410 --> 00:20:01,140
Get down.

217
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:14,290
Chu Huaiming!

218
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:20,820
He thought after the Dragon-Cracking Stone fell, he'd still be able to live for three days.

219
00:20:20,820 --> 00:20:25,700
Right now, they still have a hope of survival, but after three days, that will be gone.

220
00:20:25,700 --> 00:20:27,510
They can only die then.

221
00:20:27,510 --> 00:20:30,510
But once the mechanism is turned on...

222
00:20:30,510 --> 00:20:34,750
Getting killed now will be the most painful.

223
00:20:34,750 --> 00:20:38,860
Turns out they already set up a trap for us to die right here.

224
00:20:38,860 --> 00:20:41,930
Didn't we all volunteer to be buried?

225
00:20:41,930 --> 00:20:45,090
Why are they still doing this to us?

226
00:20:47,590 --> 00:20:52,180
We have to trigger the switch to open the door and get out.

227
00:20:54,640 --> 00:20:56,320
Be careful.

228
00:21:19,550 --> 00:21:21,000
I'll pull it.

229
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:22,400
Come and help.

230
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:24,250
- Let's go. 
 - Let's go.

231
00:21:30,210 --> 00:21:31,840
Be careful.

232
00:21:33,450 --> 00:21:35,120
Let's go.

233
00:21:43,750 --> 00:21:45,480
- Come on. 
 - Go.

234
00:21:45,480 --> 00:21:46,680
Go.

235
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:47,890
Go.

236
00:22:06,250 --> 00:22:08,580
Put the shield up.

237
00:22:10,100 --> 00:22:11,250
What do we do?

238
00:22:11,250 --> 00:22:12,510
We're the only ones left.

239
00:22:12,510 --> 00:22:15,090
We can't block them.

240
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:20,170
Don't give up.

241
00:22:20,170 --> 00:22:22,190
Try again.

242
00:22:22,730 --> 00:22:24,170
Zang Hai.

243
00:22:24,170 --> 00:22:26,340
Get on my shoulder.

244
00:22:26,340 --> 00:22:28,010
Come up!

245
00:22:28,010 --> 00:22:29,670
Go.

246
00:22:54,690 --> 00:22:56,490
Hold on.

247
00:22:56,970 --> 00:22:57,970
Almost there.

248
00:22:57,970 --> 00:22:59,700
Again.

249
00:23:45,350 --> 00:23:47,900
It's open! Higher!

250
00:24:13,300 --> 00:24:14,940
Let's go.

251
00:24:17,010 --> 00:24:19,140
Come on. Get up.

252
00:24:19,140 --> 00:24:20,720
The door is open. We're going home.

253
00:24:20,720 --> 00:24:22,960
- Get up. 
 - We're going home. Get up!

254
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:25,150
Get up!

255
00:24:36,960 --> 00:24:38,660
Let's go.

256
00:24:40,300 --> 00:24:42,340
Let's go.

257
00:24:42,340 --> 00:24:44,540
Get up. Get up.

258
00:24:44,540 --> 00:24:47,060
Get up. We're going home. Get up.

259
00:24:47,060 --> 00:24:48,820
Let's go. Come on.

260
00:24:48,820 --> 00:24:50,540
We're going home!

261
00:24:50,540 --> 00:24:51,680
Let's go.

262
00:24:51,680 --> 00:24:53,050
Let's go.

263
00:25:10,100 --> 00:25:11,870
Let's go.

264
00:25:17,580 --> 00:25:19,630
Zang Hai.

265
00:25:22,100 --> 00:25:25,390
Come on. Move!

